{"type":"message","id":"daabfed7","parentId":"a3c028d5","timestamp":"2026-04-27T23:41:03.801Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"019dd1515c0684f910c9aad943c65811","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"rules:\n- id: py-dangerous-subprocess-shell\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: subprocess call with shell=True can lead to command injection\n  severity: ERROR\n  patterns:\n  - pattern: subprocess.run($CMD, shell=True, ...)\n  - pattern-inside: |\n      import subprocess\n      ...\n- id: py-eval-exec\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: use of eval/exec allows execution of arbitrary code\n  severity: ERROR\n  pattern-either:\n  - pattern: eval($X)\n  - pattern: exec($X)\n  - pattern: getattr(os, $X)(...)\n  - pattern: getattr(subprocess, $X)(...)\n- id: py-open-sensitive-path\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: reading sensitive system path\n  severity: WARNING\n  pattern-either:\n  - pattern: open(\"/etc/\" + $X, ...)\n  - pattern: open(\"/etc/$X\", ...)\n  - pattern: open(\"/root/\" + $X, ...)\n  - pattern: open(\"/root/$X\", ...)\n  - pattern: open(\"~/.ssh/\" + $X, ...)\n  - pattern: open(\"~/.ssh/$X\", ...)\n- id: js-child-process-exec\n  languages:\n  - javascript\n  - typescript\n  message: child_process exec may allow command injection\n  severity: ERROR\n  patterns:\n  - pattern: $CP.exec($CMD, ...)\n  - pattern-inside: |\n      const $CP = require('child_process')\n      ...\n- id: js-eval\n  languages:\n  - javascript\n  - typescript\n  message: eval allows execution of arbitrary code\n  severity: ERROR\n  pattern: eval($X)\n- id: py-requests-sensitive-data\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Sending potentially sensitive data ($KEY) over network\n  severity: WARNING\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: \"requests.$METHOD(..., data={..., $KEY: $VAL, ...}, ...)\"\n    - pattern: \"requests.$METHOD(..., json={..., $KEY: $VAL, ...}, ...)\"\n  - metavariable-regex:\n      metavariable: $KEY\n      regex: (?i).*(password|secret|token|auth|key).*\n- id: py-hardcoded-secret\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Possible hardcoded secret assigned to variable\n  severity: WARNING\n  patterns:\n  - pattern: '$VAR = \"$SECRET\"'\n  - metavariable-regex:\n      metavariable: $VAR\n      regex: (?i)(password|secret|token|api_key|access_key)\n  - metavariable-regex:\n      metavariable: $SECRET\n      regex: .{8,}\n- id: py-chmod-777\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Setting file permissions to 777 (world writable/executable) is insecure\n  severity: ERROR\n  pattern-either:\n  - pattern: os.chmod(..., 0o777)\n  - pattern: os.chmod(..., 511)\n- id: py-subprocess-sudo\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Execution of command with 'sudo' detected. This indicates privilege escalation risk.\n  severity: ERROR\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: subprocess.$FUNC([\"sudo\", ...], ...)\n    - pattern: subprocess.$FUNC(\"sudo ...\", ...)\n    - pattern: os.system(\"sudo ...\")\n- id: py-pip-install-execution\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Dynamic installation of packages via pip detected. This poses a supply chain risk.\n  severity: WARNING\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: subprocess.run([\"pip\", \"install\", ...], ...)\n    - pattern: subprocess.call([\"pip\", \"install\", ...], ...)\n    - pattern: os.system(\"pip install ...\")\n- id: py-local-file-exfiltration\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Potential exfiltration of local files. Script iterates over files and sends network requests within the loop.\n  severity: WARNING\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern-inside: |\n        for $ROOT, $DIRS, $FILES in os.walk(...):\n            ...\n    - pattern-inside: |\n        for $FILE in glob.glob(...):\n            ...\n    - pattern-inside: |\n        for $FILE in pathlib.Path(...).rglob(...):\n            ...\n    - pattern-inside: |\n        for $FILE in os.listdir(...):\n            ...\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: requests.$METHOD(...)\n    - pattern: urllib.request.urlopen(...)\n    - pattern: http.client.$CONN(...).request(...)\n- id: py-dynamic-import\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Dynamic import detected. This can be used to hide dependencies or evade static analysis.\n  severity: WARNING\n  pattern-either:\n  - pattern: __import__($X)\n  - pattern: importlib.import_module($X)\n  - pattern: importlib.__import__($X)\n- id: py-socket-usage\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Low-level socket usage detected. This can be used to bypass HTTP library checks.\n  severity: WARNING\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: socket.socket(...)\n    - pattern: socket.create_connection(...)\n    - pattern: $SOCK.connect(...)\n    - pattern: $SOCK.send(...)\n    - pattern: $SOCK.sendall(...)\n  - pattern-inside: |\n      import socket\n      ...\n- id: py-pickle-deserialize\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Unsafe deserialization detected (pickle). This can lead to Remote Code Execution (RCE). Use secure alternatives like json.\n  severity: ERROR\n  pattern-either:\n  - pattern: pickle.loads(...)\n  - pattern: pickle.load(...)\n  - pattern: _pickle.loads(...)\n  - pattern: _pickle.load(...)\n  - pattern: cPickle.loads(...)\n  - pattern: cPickle.load(...)\n- id: cap-network\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Capability - Network Access\n  severity: INFO\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: requests.$METHOD(...)\n    - pattern: urllib.request.urlopen(...)\n    - pattern: http.client.$CONN(...).request(...)\n    - pattern: socket.socket(...)\n    - pattern: socket.create_connection(...)\n- id: cap-filesystem-write\n  languages:\n  - python\n  message: Capability - File System Write\n  severity: INFO\n  patterns:\n  - pattern-either:\n    - pattern: open(..., \"w\")\n    - pattern: open(..., \"wb\")\n    - pattern: open(..., \"a\")\n    - pattern: $PATH.write_text(...)\n    - pattern: $PATH.write_bytes(...)\n    - pattern: pickle.dump(...)\n- id: cap-command-exe